data:
The T stage is determined by the size of the primary tumor.
T1: tumor size ≤ 2 cm, T2: tumor size > 2 cm but ≤ 5 cm, T3: tumor size > 5 cm
The N stage is determined by the involvement of lymph nodes.
N0: no regional lymph node metastasis, N1: metastasis in 1-3 axillary lymph nodes
The M stage is determined by the presence of distant metastasis.
M0: no distant metastasis, M1: distant metastasis
If the M stage is not specified, it is denoted as 'Mx'

The T stage is determined by the size of the primary tumor.
T1: tumor size ≤ 2 cm, T2: tumor size > 2 cm but ≤ 5 cm, T3: tumor size > 5 cm
The N stage is determined by the involvement of lymph nodes.
N0: no regional lymph node metastasis, N1: metastasis in 1-3 axillary lymph nodes
The M stage is determined by the presence of distant metastasis.
M0: no distant metastasis, M1: distant metastasis
If the M stage is not specified, it is denoted as 'Mx'
The number of involved lymph nodes and the presence of extranodal extension are used to determine the N stage
The presence of distant metastasis is used to determine the M stage

The number of involved lymph nodes and the presence of extranodal extension are used to determine the N stage
The presence of distant metastasis is used to determine the M stage
The T stage is based solely on the size of the primary tumor, regardless of other factors such as margin status or lymphovascular invasion.
